title: Unconventional Commands
story: guess-the-verb
description: Commands that feel valid in English but aren't standard IF — tests disambiguation and parser coverage

---

## Front Porch — alternate verbs and nouns

> look
[OK: contains "Front Porch"]

# Alternate nouns for doormat
> examine mat
[OK: contains "doormat"]

> examine rug
[OK: contains "doormat"]

# Alternate nouns for doorbell
> examine bell
[OK: contains_any "brass" "button" "doorbell"]

> examine buzzer
[OK: contains_any "brass" "button" "doorbell"]

# Natural verb: knock
> knock on door
[OK: contains_any "door" "knock" "no one" "nobody" "locked"]

# "flip" the mat — physical manipulation (parser doesn't know "flip")
> flip mat
[OK: contains_any "doormat" "key" "flip" "can't" "don't understand"]

# "check under" — natural search phrasing
> check under mat
[OK: contains_any "key" "doormat" "under"]

# Use-based phrasing (very common from non-IF players)
> use key
[OK: contains_any "key" "use" "can't see"]

> look under doormat
[OK: contains "key"]

> take key
[OK: contains "Taken"]

> use key on door
[OK: contains_any "unlock" "key" "door" "use"]

> unlock door with key
[OK: contains "unlock"]

> open door
[OK: contains "open"]

> go east
[OK: contains "Hallway"]

## Hallway — alternate nouns and search phrasing

# "coat" for "overcoat"
> examine coat
[OK: contains_any "overcoat" "coat" "wool"]

# "check" as examine synonym
> check overcoat
[OK: contains_any "overcoat" "coat" "wool"]

# Part-of-noun: pockets
> look in pockets
[OK: contains_any "pockets" "matches" "matchbook" "overcoat"]

> search overcoat
[OK: contains_any "matches" "matchbook" "pockets"]

# Direction synonyms
# "go upstairs" — not recognized as direction
> go upstairs
[OK: contains_any "Attic" "up" "UP" "stairs" "can't" "which direction"]

# "ascend" — not a recognized verb
> ascend
[OK: contains_any "Attic" "up" "UP" "can't" "don't understand"]

## Study — fire, painting, and safe puzzles

> east
[OK: contains "Study"]

> open desk
[OK: contains "open"]

> take winding key
[OK: contains_any "Taken" "winding"]

# "picture" and "portrait" for painting
> examine picture
[OK: contains_any "painting" "portrait" "picture" "oil"]

> examine portrait
[OK: contains_any "painting" "portrait" "picture" "oil"]

# "look behind" — very natural English
> look behind painting
[OK: contains_any "painting" "safe" "wall"]

# "slide" the painting
> slide painting
[OK: contains_any "painting" "safe" "wall" "can't" "slide"]

# Fire verbs — "start fire", "ignite"
> ignite fireplace
[OK: contains_any "fire" "match" "glow" "warmth" "can't" "ignite"]

> start fire
[OK: contains_any "fire" "match" "burn" "what" "can't"]

> light fireplace
[OK: contains_any "fire" "match" "glow" "warmth" "7" "hearthstone"]

# Alternate nouns for hearthstone
# "hearth" resolves to fireplace, not hearthstone
> examine hearth
[OK: contains_any "hearthstone" "hearth" "fireplace" "flames" "fire" "stone" "7"]

# Try opening safe before combo — should say something about needing the combo
# (Note: safe was already opened by dial, so "open safe" on already-open safe = blank — engine bug)
> open safe
[OK: contains_any "safe" "combo" "combination" "locked" "dial" "Click" "already" "open"]

> dial 7 3 9
[OK: contains_any "Click" "click" "open"]

> take clock spring
[OK: contains_any "Taken" "spring"]

## Kitchen — passing through

> west
[OK: contains "Hallway"]

> south
[OK: contains "Kitchen"]

# Kitchen atmospheric attempts
> turn faucet
[OK: contains_any "faucet" "water" "tap" "turn" "can't"]

> read recipe
[OK: contains_any "recipe" "read" "can't see"]

## Garden — dig variations

> south
[OK: contains "Garden"]

> take trowel
[OK: contains "Taken"]

# "use trowel" — generic USE
> use trowel
[OK: contains_any "trowel" "dig" "use" "can't"]

# Alternate dig nouns
> dig dirt
[OK: contains_any "dig" "flower" "earth" "mechanism" "soft"]

> dig ground
[OK: contains_any "dig" "flower" "earth" "mechanism" "soft" "ground"]

> dig soil
[OK: contains_any "dig" "flower" "earth" "mechanism" "soft" "soil"]

# "excavate" as dig synonym
> excavate flower bed
[OK: contains_any "dig" "flower" "mechanism" "excavate" "can't"]

> take mechanism
[OK: contains_any "Taken" "mechanism" "already"]

## Attic — assembly and winding variations

> north
[OK: contains "Kitchen"]

> north
[OK: contains "Hallway"]

> up
[OK: contains "Attic"]

> take music box
[OK: contains "music box"]

# Assembly synonyms
> attach mechanism to music box
[OK: contains_any "mechanism" "attach" "put" "music box" "can't"]

> put mechanism in music box
[OK: contains "mechanism"]

# "install" as insert synonym
> install spring in music box
[OK: contains_any "spring" "install" "put" "music box" "can't"]

> put spring in music box
[OK: contains "spring"]

# "fix" / "repair" as assembly verbs
> fix music box
[OK: contains_any "music box" "fix" "repair" "can't" "wind"]

# Wind variations
> crank music box
[OK: contains_any "melody" "crank" "wind" "can't"]

> wind up music box
[OK: contains_any "melody" "wind" "release" "trunk" "can't"]

> wind music box with key
[OK: contains_any "melody" "wind" "release" "trunk" "key"]

> wind music box
[OK: contains_any "melody" "wind" "release" "trunk"]

> open trunk
[OK: contains_any "open" "trunk" "locket"]

> take locket
[OK: contains "locket"]
